I am happy to announce that I successfully completed #Springboard's Data Science Career Track Program! 
I am so glad to have taken this next step in my professional career. 
I wish to thank all the mentors, as well as the career coaches for their support through this long journey.
I am grateful for my family and friends that helped motivate me during this time in my life.

#DATA is everywhere, if you can only imagine how managing data can change life (health, natural disaster, business, economy, planning, sustainability, species management...), it is absolutely amazing!

After 8 months of hard work, I set up a solid foundation to build on, and I look forward to face real-world data problems to strengthen my skills.

text.text:
Call for Applications for student project under ICRAF Fellowship Program 2020

ICRAF is inviting applications from qualified candidates to work under the newly formed Transformative partnership platform (TPP)-- Nutri-scapes. Nutri-scapes is seeking interested young researchers from the nutrition or social science fields that want to contribute to the goals of the platform. 

If you have an idea for a research project that would contribute to the goals of the platform to solve nutrition challenges in developing countries, submit a short proposal outlining the idea, the proposed timeline and the required budget up to approximately USD 3,000. 

The funds can be used for; a stipend at an approved rate, research costs, fieldwork (where possible), medical and accident insurances, any other costs depending on the type of project proposed.

Due to the current difficulties in conducting field research we are especially interested in ideas that look at existing data or literature and contribute to the theoretical underpinnings or collate existing knowledge. The aim should be a publication.
Please send your proposal along with your CV latest by August 20th, 2020.
Get more details and apply here: https://lnkd.in/d-_2KKu

title.text: Expert-assisted Decision Analysis supports agroforestry in Viet Nam

text.text:
Decision-makers on agricultural systems, from farmers to agricultural ministers, should consider ecosystem services, such as water regulation, soil protection, and biodiversity conservation and their trade-offs, but this rarely happens. Selecting appropriate practices for specific locations that are aligned with the needs, values and priorities of farmers is difficult. Researchers are using Decision Analysis to overcome the challenge.

Learn how researchers from World Agroforestry (ICRAF) and  The University of Bonn are using Decision Analysis approaches to support agroforestry in Viet Nam.
